cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.CE 

This paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for time series prediction in the context of intelligent building management. The paper focuses on the use of an ancillary neural network to capture weekend and holiday information, which is a unique aspect of the proposed architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of long short-term memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly used in neural network-based time series prediction, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper is related to the field of civil engineering, which could make cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) a relevant sub-category as well.
